frameDefinitions: In this frame a Patient is in a state of having been broken into smaller pieces.  '
An Agent suddenly and often violently separates the Whole_patient into two or more smaller Pieces, resulting in the Whole_patient no longer existing as such.
In this frame a Grinder or Grinding_cause causes a Patient to be broken into smaller pieces.
An Entity has a particular scalar Attribute with a value exceeding a contextually-specified or generally-understood standard.
This frame contains words that describe an Item's static position on a scale with respect to some property Variable.  '' 'Dried fruits are especially high in fibre, as are pulses.'
An Entity has a Sharpness characterized by its capability to cut.
frameExamples: He <t>ripped</t> <t>up</t> the letter faster than you can say 'Jack Robbins'. INI
Bill <t>ground</t> the coffee beans into a fine powder.
Dried fruits are especially <t>high</t> in fibre, as are pulses.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity acted on and that undergoes a change.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs the intentional action that results in the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> being broken into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The entity which is destroyed by the <fen>Agent</fen> and that ends up broken into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The fragments of the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> that result from the <fen>Agent</fen>'s action.
An event which leads to the fragmentation of the <fen>Whole_patient</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> breaks up the <fen>Whole_patient</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> breaks the <fen>Whole_patient</fen> into pieces.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that grinds. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic.
The <fen>Grinder</fen> breaks the <fen>Patient</fen> into smaller pieces.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity which undergoes the change brought about by the <fen>Grinder</fen> or <fen>Grinding_cause</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when  the <fen>Grinder</fen> grinds the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where  the <fen>Grinder</fen> grinds the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular gradable <fen>Attribute</fen> is appropriate and under consideration.
The feature of an <fen>Entity</fen> which is under discussion.
A quantity or other characterization of the <fen>Entity</fen>'s state with respect to the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Value</fen> from the norm.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having  a particular <fen>Value</fen> for the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
<fen>Item</fen> identifies the entity whose scalar property is specified.

<fen>Variable</fen> is the scalar property that the <fen>Item</fen> possesses.

<fex name='Item'>Soda</fex> is <t>high</t> <fex name='Variable'>in sugar</fex>.
The <fen>Value</fen> is the position or range of positions on the scale that the Item occupies.  This is normally implicit in the LU.
The <fen>Entity</fen> to which the <fen>Sharpness</fen> attribute is related.
The sharpness feature of the <fen>Entity</fen>.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Sharpness</fen> from the norm or from the value for another <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Sharpness</fen> value of the <fen>Entity</fen>.  This role is denoted by the adjectives of the frame.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having  a particular value for <fen>Sharpness</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>I and I alone</fex> can shatter the gem and break the curse.
Shattering someone's confidence is a little different than shattering <fex>a dish</fex>.
I smashed the toy boat <fex>to flinders</fex>.
<fex>The wind</fex> ground the leaves into a fine powder.
